This command is used if TW is called with `npm run serve`.

IMPORTANT: It can ''only'' be used with: `npm run`!

```
npm run serve
```

Default config parameters are:

* "serve_edition": "./editions/tw5.com-server"
* "serve_port" : "8080"
* "serve_host": ""
* "verbose": "--verbose"

Parameters can be changed with eg:

`npm config set tiddlywiki:serve_editon ./editions/xyz`

use: `npm config --help`

or see: https://www.npmjs.org/doc/misc/npm-scripts.html